bitfield.description: TI internal data. Identifies revision of peripheral.

Reads return 0 and writes have no effect.
Priority level for each inbound transaction on the internal bus master port. 0 is the highest priority level and 7h is the lowest priority level.
Reads return 0 and writes have no effect.

EOI for interrupts. Write the interrupt event number to indicate end-of-interrupt for the interrupt events. Write 0 to mark EOI for INTA, 1 for INTB and so on. Please see the for the interrupt event number.

This register is written to by the remote device. Writes initiated by an EP over PCIe link that targetPCIE_BAR0 of the RC land to this register if the offset matches. EP should write MSI vector value to this register to generate corresponding MSI Interrupt, such as writing 0x0 to generate MSI_0 interrupt (with vector 0), writing 0x1F to generate MSI_7 interrupt (with vector 31).
Reads return 0 and writes have no effect.
Write 1 to generate assert interrupt message. If MSI is disabled, legacy interrupt assert message will be generated. On read, a 1 indicates currently asserted interrupt.
Reads return 0 and writes have no effect.
Write 1 to generate deassert interrupt message. If MSI is disabled, legacy interrupt deassert message will be generated. On read, a 1 indicates currently asserted interrupt.
Reads return 0 and writes have no effect.
Indicates whether interrupt for function 0 is asserted or not.
